        <item>
            <title>K Kwong：我唔想食紙   「紙餐具多有害化學物質、比想像污糟」</title>
            <link>https://unwire.hk/2024/04/25/paper-is-dirty-said-by-k-kwong/life-tech/green-2/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=paper-is-dirty-said-by-k-kwong</link>
            <comments>https://unwire.hk/2024/04/25/paper-is-dirty-said-by-k-kwong/life-tech/green-2/#respond</comments>
            <dc:creator>
                <![CDATA[Oscar]]>
            </dc:creator>
            <pubDate>Thu, 25 Apr 2024 07:20:01 +0000</pubDate>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[環保]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[紙餐具]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[走塑]]>
            </category>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://unwire.hk/?p=1231232</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[<p>首階段即棄膠餐具和塑膠產品管制已於本月 22 日正式實施，行政長官李家超早前表示「走塑」對市民影響不大（<a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/04/23/john-lee-said-no-plastic-doesnot-affect-citizen/life-tech/green-2/">相關報道</a>），但前化學科補習導師「Dr. K. Kwong」就表示，紙餐具除了不環保外，更比想像中「污糟」。</p><p>K Kwong 表示部份紙有 polychlorinated dibenzo-p-dioxins （PCDDs）、polychlorinated dibenzofurans （PCDFs）、polychlorinated biphenyls（PCBs），並分享了不少外國研究結果，大部份均表示紙杯含有有毒化學物質，而且與塑膠杯相比，紙杯並沒有更加環保。研究顯示，紙杯具有耐水耐熱的 PFAS 化學物質，會污染承載的飲料。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231233" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439432924_9631613585-445x580.jpg" alt="" width="445" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439432924_9631613585-445x580.jpg 445w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439432924_9631613585.jpg 584w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 445px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲圖片來源：<a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a></p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231234" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439456305_9631613851-441x580.jpg" alt="" width="441" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439456305_9631613851-441x580.jpg 441w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439456305_9631613851.jpg 684w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 441px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲圖片來源：<a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231235" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439438046_9631614085-451x580.jpg" alt="" width="451" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439438046_9631614085-451x580.jpg 451w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439438046_9631614085.jpg 700w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 451px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲圖片來源：<a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231236" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439482340_9631613751-694x468.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="468" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439482340_9631613751-694x468.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439482340_9631613751.jpg 1254w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲圖片來源：<a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231237" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439586213_9631614185-359x580.jpg" alt="" width="359" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439586213_9631614185-359x580.jpg 359w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439586213_9631614185.jpg 557w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 359px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲圖片來源：<a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a></p><p>K Kwong 表示，紙張本來就只應該用來印書寫字，不應該用來製造餐具。K Kwong 稱自己不會使用紙製餐具，因為造紙過程使用大量酸（H2SO4）、鹼 (NaOH）、漂白劑 （Cl2，Cl2O，SO2）、螢光劑、防腐劑等，K Kwong 更指一張紙有過百種有害化學品，因此他自己不僅不使用紙餐具，甚至連用紙巾抹筷子、匙羹也不會。</p><p>K Kwong 另外又指紙張會吸水，倘若要用作製作餐具之原材料就必須加上防水塗層，紙包飲品塗層有塑膠、鋁；紙餐具除了防水更要防油，所以或會加入含有 PFAS 的 Teflon，而紙餐具吸水後會變軟，如是者又要加入填充物。K Kwong 指，現行法律並未規管填充物，因此廠商會選用非食用級的材質，如 CaCO3、TiO2。</p><div class="x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s x126k92a"><div dir="auto"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231238" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/20240425135530-694x416.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="416" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/20240425135530-694x416.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/20240425135530.jpg 705w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></div></div><p>資料來源： <a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a></p><br /><b>相關文章:</b><blockquote><li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/04/25/bamboo-knife-cut-steak-broke-twice/life-tech/green-2/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">【走塑】供應商示範竹刀叉鋸扒但兩度截斷，負責人：市民需時間適應</a></li>&nbsp;<li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/04/23/john-lee-said-no-plastic-doesnot-affect-citizen/life-tech/green-2/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">李家超：「走塑」對市民影響不大，謝展寰：如替代餐具不耐用可試其他產品</a></li>&nbsp;<li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/04/23/netizen-sell-disposable-spoon-3000-hkd/life-tech/green-2/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">網民售賣快餐店絕版塑膠餐具，標價 HK$3,000 不議價送紙巾</a></li>&nbsp;</blockquote><br /><p>The post <a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/04/25/paper-is-dirty-said-by-k-kwong/life-tech/green-2/">K Kwong：我唔想食紙   「紙餐具多有害化學物質、比想像污糟」</a> appeared first on <a href="https://unwire.hk">UNWIRE.HK</a>.</p>
]]>
            </description>
